Description: This Python project utilizes the Pandas library for data manipulation and analysis of a Superstore's sales dataset. It covers various aspects including order priority, shipping modes, customer segments, product categories, and geographical analysis. The project visualizes data using Seaborn and Matplotlib to gain insights into sales patterns, profit margins, and regional performance. By exploring different dimensions of the dataset, it offers a comprehensive understanding of the Superstore's operations, aiding in decision-making processes

# Draw a graph for top 10  State or Province sales analysis
top_10state_sales=f.groupby(["State or Province"],as_index=False)["Sales"].sum().sort_values(by="Sales",ascending=False).head(10)
pt.figure(figsize=(15,4))
ax=sns.barplot(x="State or Province",y="Sales",data=top_10state_sales,hue="State or Province")
pt.title("Top 10 state Sales vise sum")
for bars in ax.containers:
    ax.bar_label(bars)

region_sales_sum = f.groupby('Region')['Sales'].sum()
# Draw a Pie Chart for region vise sales Analysis
pt.figure(figsize=(5, 3))
region_sales_sum.plot.pie(autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90,shadow=True,explode=[0,0,0,0.1] )
pt.title('Region-wise Sales Sum')
pt.ylabel('')
pt.show()

Conclusion This project provides insights into various aspects of sales data for a superstore, helping identify trends and areas for improvement. Visualizations such as bar graphs and pie charts effectively convey the distribution of key metrics, facilitating data-driven decision-making. By following this detailed analysis, stakeholders can better understand customer preferences, optimize inventory, and improve overall sales strategies.
